    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1915-03-26T23:59:59-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1915-03-26T00:00:00-05:00" n="1391"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d1391">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">File No. 812.512/583.</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Secretary of State</gloss> to the
                            <gloss type="to">Brazilian Minister to Mexico</gloss>
                    </hi>.</head>
                <opener>
                    <seg rendition="#center">[Telegram.]</seg>
                </opener>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Department of State</hi>, <lb/>
                            <hi rend="italic">Washington</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1915-03-26">
                            <hi rend="italic">March 26, 1915</hi>
                        </date>.</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>Please request appropriate authorities advise you immediately whether Governor
                    Cantú, functioning Ensenada, is subject to orders from Mexico City, and if so to
                    whom and how taxes on mining property Lower California may be paid. Also please
                    request that, owing to existing confusion, no action be taken looking to
                    forfeiture American-owned property that section for non-payment taxes.</p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">W. J. Bryan.</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
